page.title: 13 Visit to Vobster church.
page.content: On Thursday July the 4th I went to St. Edmund's church. I went with six other boys. When we got there the vicar was waiting for us. We all said hello. He said," First of all we can all sit down on the grass and I will tell you about little odd things." The first thing he told us was about St.Edmund. St.Edmund was tied to a tree and had arrows shot at him. Then they cut off his head to say that he was really dead. Then we all went into the church to have a look around. We went into a little room and we saw an old rusty safe.Then we looked around a bit more and we found the key to the safe. We saw a big eagle and it was very beautiful indeed. Then we did some drawings.
